headline: Cisco Unveils Quantum Chip And Lab To Push Next-Gen Networking
summary: Cisco Systems, Inc. (NASDAQ:CSCO) announced on Tuesday that it has created a new quantum chip in collaboration with UC Santa Barbara that enables quantum networks to scale and connect quantum processors for practical applications. The company also said it opened a quantum lab in Santa Monica, CA, where quantum scientists and engineers are building quantum networking technologies. headline: Cisco Study Reveals Alarming Deficiencies in Security Readiness
summary: According to Cisco's (NASDAQ: CSCO) 2025 Cybersecurity Readiness Index, only 4% of organizations worldwide have achieved the 'Mature' level of readiness required to effectively withstand today's cybersecurity threats. This is a slight increase from last year's Index, in which 3% of organizations worldwide were designated as Mature.
